Key.Original: A single death is a tragedy; a million deaths is a statistic.
Key.English: A single death is a tragedy; a million deaths is a statistic.

Key.Original: Stay out of the road, if you want to grow old.
Key.English: Stay out of the road, if you want to grow old.

Key.Original: Death is a very dull, dreary affair, and my advice to you is to have nothing whatsoever to do with it.
Key.English: Death is a very dull, dreary affair, and my advice to you is to have nothing whatsoever to do with it.

Key.Original: Many that live deserve death. And some that die deserve life.
Key.English: Many that live deserve death. And some that die deserve life.

Key.Original: And lastly there is the oldest and deepest desire, the Great Escape: the Escape from Death.
Key.English: And lastly there is the oldest and deepest desire, the Great Escape: the Escape from Death.

Key.Original: As to you, Life, I reckon you are the leavings of many deaths; No doubt I have died, myself ten thousand times before.
Key.English: As to you, Life, I reckon you are the leavings of many deaths; No doubt I have died, myself ten thousand times before.

Key.Original: Men are at war with each other because each man is at war with himself.
Key.English: Men are at war with each other because each man is at war with himself.

Key.Original: It's not that I'm afraid to die, I just don't want to be there when it happens.
Key.English: It's not that I'm afraid to die, I just don't want to be there when it happens.

Key.Original: It is hard to have patience with people who say 'There is no death' or 'Death doesn't matter.' There is death and whatever is matters.
Key.English: It is hard to have patience with people who say 'There is no death' or 'Death doesn't matter.' There is death and whatever is matters.

Key.Original: A man's dying is more the survivors' affair than his own.
Key.English: A man's dying is more the survivors' affair than his own.

Key.Original: I do not believe in a fate that falls on men however they act; but I do believe in a fate that falls on them unless they act.
Key.English: I do not believe in a fate that falls on men however they act; but I do believe in a fate that falls on them unless they act.

Key.Original: I believe that people would be alive today if there were a death penalty.
Key.English: I believe that people would be alive today if there were a death penalty.

Key.Original: A man who won't die for something is not fit to live.
Key.English: A man who won't die for something is not fit to live.

Key.Original: Once the game is over, the king and the pawn go back in the same box.
Key.English: Once the game is over, the king and the pawn go back in the same box.

Key.Original: I have not yet begun to fight!
Key.English: I have not yet begun to fight!

Key.Original: Mankind must put an end to war, or war will put an end to mankind.
Key.English: Mankind must put an end to war, or war will put an end to mankind.

Key.Original: Wars have never hurt anybody except the people who die.
Key.English: Wars have never hurt anybody except the people who die.

Key.Original: War does not determine who is right - only who is left.
Key.English: War does not determine who is right - only who is left.

Key.Original: We improve ourselves by victories over ourself. There must be contests, and you must win.
Key.English: We improve ourselves by victories over ourself. There must be contests, and you must win.

Key.Original: We succeed only as we identify in life, or in war, or in anything else, a single overriding objective, and make all other considerations bend to that one objective.
Key.English: We succeed only as we identify in life, or in war, or in anything else, a single overriding objective, and make all other considerations bend to that one objective.

Key.Original: Experience is a hard teacher because she gives the test first, the lesson afterwards.
Key.English: Experience is a hard teacher because she gives the test first, the lesson afterwards.

Key.Original: You might as well fall flat on your face as lean over too far backwards.
Key.English: You might as well fall flat on your face as lean over too far backwards.

Key.Original: The quickest way to end a war is to lose it.
Key.English: The quickest way to end a war is to lose it.

Key.Original: Courage is being scared to death - but saddling up anyway.
Key.English: Courage is being scared to death - but saddling up anyway.

Key.Original: Death is more universal than life; everyone dies but not everyone lives.
Key.English: Death is more universal than life; everyone dies but not everyone lives.

Key.Original: Imagination is the one weapon in the war against reality.
Key.English: Imagination is the one weapon in the war against reality.

Key.Original: You can't say that civilization don't advance, however, for in every war they kill you in a new way.
Key.English: You can't say that civilization don't advance, however, for in every war they kill you in a new way.

Key.Original: . . .Sometime they'll give a war and nobody will come.
Key.English: . . .Sometime they'll give a war and nobody will come.

Key.Original: It is well that war is so terrible, or we should get too fond of it.
Key.English: It is well that war is so terrible, or we should get too fond of it.

Key.Original: You can no more win a war than you can win an earthquake.
Key.English: You can no more win a war than you can win an earthquake.

Key.Original: War is one of the scourges with which it has pleased God to afflict men.
Key.English: War is one of the scourges with which it has pleased God to afflict men.

Key.Original: In war there is no substitute for victory.
Key.English: In war there is no substitute for victory.

Key.Original: War isn't about who's right, its about who's left.
Key.English: War isn't about who's right, its about who's left.

Key.Original: I know not with what weapons World War III will be fought, but World War IV will be fought with sticks and stones.
Key.English: I know not with what weapons World War III will be fought, but World War IV will be fought with sticks and stones.

Key.Original: The object of war is not to die for your country but to make the other bastard die for his.
Key.English: The object of war is not to die for your country but to make the other bastard die for his.

Key.Original: Much good work is lost for the lack of a little more.
Key.English: Much good work is lost for the lack of a little more.

Key.Original: When defeat comes, accept it as a signal that your plans are not sound, rebuild those plans, and set sail once more toward your coveted goal.
Key.English: When defeat comes, accept it as a signal that your plans are not sound, rebuild those plans, and set sail once more toward your coveted goal.

Key.Original: War is much too serious a matter to be entrusted to the military.
Key.English: War is much too serious a matter to be entrusted to the military.

Key.Original: War is a series of disasters which result in a winner.
Key.English: War is a series of disasters which result in a winner.

Key.Original: War is a game that is played with a smile. If you can't smile, grin. If you can't grin, keep out of the way till you can.
Key.English: War is a game that is played with a smile. If you can't smile, grin. If you can't grin, keep out of the way till you can.

Key.Original: To be prepared for war is one of the most effective means of preserving peace.
Key.English: To be prepared for war is one of the most effective means of preserving peace.

Key.English: Brave men are all vertebrates; they have their softness on the surface and their toughness in the middle.
